285 g Shrimp
200 g Chow Mein Noodles
170 g Vegetable Mix
1 unit Green Onion
¼ cup Vegetarian Oyster Sauce
4 tbsp Teriyaki Sauce
2 tbsp Ginger-Garlic Puree
9 g Sesame Seeds
1 tbsp Sesame Oil
1 tbsp Butter*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, to a large pot, add 10 cups water and 2 tsp salt (use the same for 4 servings). Cover and bring to a boil over high heat.
Thinly slice scallions.
To a medium bowl, add teriyaki sauce, oyster sauce, sesame oil and 1/4 cup (1/3 cup) water. Whisk to combine.
Using a strainer, drain and rinse shrimp, then pat dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, shrimp, sesame seeds and half the green onions. Cook for 2-3 min, stirring occasionally, until sesame seeds are toasted and shrimp just turn pink.** (NOTE: For 4 servings, cook in two batches with half the sesame seeds and 1 tbsp oil per batch.)
Transfer shrimp to a plate and cover to keep warm.

Add chow mein noodles to the boiling water. Cook uncovered for 1-2 min, until tender.
Drain noodles, then rinse under warm water.
Return noodles to the same pot, off heat. Add 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) oil, then gently toss to coat.
Using a pair of scissors, make a few cuts in the pot to cut up noodles.
Set aside.

Reheat the same pan over medium-high.
When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, vegetable mix and 2 tbsp water. Season with salt and pepper. Cook for 3-5 min, stirring often until tender-crisp and golden.
Add ginger-garlic puree. Cook for 30 sec, stirring often until fragrant.
Add sauce mixture and 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter. Cook for 30 sec, stirring often until sauce is warmed through and butter has melted.

Add sauce mixture to pot with noodles. Stir to coat.
Divide noodles and shrimp between bowls.
Sprinkle remaining green onions overtop.